The paper presents a method for learning compliant motions for a robot, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves using machine learning techniques to learn from demonstrations, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using geometry to reduce the need for initial accuracy, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper evaluates the method on a robot, which suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
